		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">New Producer Letter</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=380941" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    A new <a href="http://www.everquest.com/main/letter.jsp">Producer Letter</a> has been put up today on the official EverQuest website. This letter talks about making Customer Service better for the players and some additions such as a player' Bill of Rights'. Here is a sniplet: 

<blockquote>
<p>
<i>As we approach the two-year anniversary of EverQuest, we can’t help but look back at the changes that have taken place in the world of Norrath. In the beginning our Customer Service Department was small and the rules both we and the players were expected to follow were still being hammered out on a day-to-day basis. We then grew quickly; as did our expectations, and as time went on we developed and refined a number of rules providing varying levels of communication between us and the player community.</i>
</p>
</blockquote>
Head over to the official site to view the latest <a href="http://www.everquest.com/main/letter.jsp">producer letter</a>!
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
